Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil your #kettle{}, then pour the @water{450%ml} into a #measuring jug{}.

Add the @vegetable stock paste{20%g} and @dried basil{1%tsp} to the jug and stir
well to combine. This is your stock.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, wide-bottomed ovenproof pan on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}. Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, stir and
cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the stock.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{})
and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water
has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and pop them onto a piece of
foil with a drizzle of oil, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Pop onto a large
#baking tray{} and roast on the bottom shelf until softened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain the @mozzarella{1} and pat it dry with #kitchen paper{}, making sure you
squeeze out as much liquid as possible. Then tear it into pieces.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the
@butter{20%g}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g},
@baby spinach{40%g} and @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}. Season to taste with
@salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Change your oven setting to grill. Set to the highest temperature.

Arrange your mozzarella on top of your risotto.

Return to the oven and place on the top shelf. Grill until golden and
bubbling, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Divide your risotto between your #serving bowls{}, top with your roasted baby
plums and drizzle over your @fresh pesto{50%g}.

Enjoy!